# Design System Rules for AI Assistant

You have access to a multi-theme design system. ALWAYS use CSS variables from this system instead of hardcoded colors or arbitrary values.

## Quick Reference

### Apply Theme
Add theme class to `<html>`:
```html
<html class="theme-health-sem">
```

Available themes: `theme-health-sem`, `theme-home-sem`, `theme-forbes-media-seo`, `theme-llm`, `theme-advisor-sem-compare-coverage`

### Color Tokens

**Backgrounds** - use `var(--color-bg-*)`
| Token | Usage |
|-------|-------|
| `--color-bg-white` | Page background |
| `--color-bg-neutral-light` | Cards, inputs |
| `--color-bg-neutral` | Section backgrounds |
| `--color-bg-brand` | Brand sections, CTAs |
| `--color-bg-header` | Navigation |
| `--color-bg-accent` | Highlights |

**Text** - use `var(--color-fg-*)`
| Token | Usage |
|-------|-------|
| `--color-fg-heading` | h1-h6 headings |
| `--color-fg-body` | Paragraphs |
| `--color-fg-caption` | Secondary text |
| `--color-fg-link` | Links |
| `--color-fg-heading-inverse` | Text on dark bg |
| `--color-fg-body-inverse` | Text on dark bg |

**Buttons** - use `var(--color-btn-*)`
```css
/* Primary button */
background: var(--color-btn-primary-bg);
color: var(--color-btn-primary-text);
/* hover state */
background: var(--color-btn-primary-hover-bg);

/* Secondary button */
background: var(--color-btn-secondary-bg);
border-color: var(--color-btn-secondary-border);
color: var(--color-btn-secondary-text);

/* Ghost button */
color: var(--color-btn-ghost-text);
/* hover */
background: var(--color-btn-ghost-hover-bg);
```

**Feedback States**
- `var(--color-fg-feedback-error)` - Errors
- `var(--color-fg-feedback-warning)` - Warnings
- `var(--color-fg-feedback-success)` - Success

### Typography Tokens

**Font Sizes** - use `var(--font-size-*)`
| Token | Size | Usage |
|-------|------|-------|
| `--font-size-display` | 56px | Hero headlines |
| `--font-size-heading-lg` | 48px | Page titles |
| `--font-size-heading-md` | 32px | Section headers |
| `--font-size-heading-sm` | 24px | Card titles |
| `--font-size-title-lg` | 20px | Subtitles |
| `--font-size-body-lg` | 18px | Lead text |
| `--font-size-body-md` | 16px | Body text |
| `--font-size-body-sm` | 14px | Secondary |
| `--font-size-label-md` | 14px | Buttons, labels |

**Font Weights**
- `var(--font-weight-regular)`: 400
- `var(--font-weight-medium)`: 500
- `var(--font-weight-semibold)`: 600
- `var(--font-weight-bold)`: 700

**Line Heights**
- `var(--line-height-sm)`: 20px
- `var(--line-height-md)`: 22px
- `var(--line-height-lg)`: 24px
- `var(--line-height-xl)`: 26px

### Spacing & Grid

```css
padding: var(--grid-gutter);  /* 24px desktop, 12px mobile */
margin: var(--grid-margin);   /* 80px desktop, 16px mobile */
```

Breakpoints:
- Mobile: < 744px
- Tablet: 744px - 1439px
- Desktop: ≥ 1440px

## Rules

1. **NEVER** use hardcoded colors like `#657E79` or `bg-blue-500`
2. **ALWAYS** use CSS variables: `var(--color-fg-heading)`
3. **ALWAYS** apply theme class to root element
4. Use semantic tokens (`fg-heading`) not generic names
5. For hover states, use the `-hover-` token variants
6. For dark backgrounds, use `-inverse` text tokens

## Examples

### ✅ Good
```jsx
<button style={{
  backgroundColor: 'var(--color-btn-primary-bg)',
  color: 'var(--color-btn-primary-text)'
}}>
  Submit
</button>

<h1 style={{
  color: 'var(--color-fg-heading)',
  fontSize: 'var(--font-size-heading-lg)'
}}>
  Welcome
</h1>
```

### ❌ Bad
```jsx
<button style={{ backgroundColor: '#657E79', color: 'white' }}>
  Submit
</button>

<h1 style={{ color: '#333', fontSize: '48px' }}>
  Welcome
</h1>
```

## With Tailwind

If using Tailwind with the design system preset:
```jsx
<button className="bg-btn-primary-bg text-btn-primary-text hover:bg-btn-primary-hover">
  Submit
</button>

<h1 className="text-fg-heading text-heading-lg font-bold">
  Welcome
</h1>

<div className="bg-bg-neutral-light p-gutter">
  Card content
</div>
```
